  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Microsoft® Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) 3.5 \n<li>Microsoft Visual Studio® 2008</li></li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>Description</h1>\n  <p>Secure conversations are turned on by default for all bindings that support ws-security. This includes wsHttpBinding, netTcpBinding, netMsmqBinding. If you are using a custom binding, turn on secure conversations with the <strong>authenticationMode</strong> attribute.</p>\n  <pre>  &lt;customBinding&gt; <br />    &lt;binding name=\"ServiceBinding\"&gt; <br />      &lt;security authenticationMode=\"SecureConversation\" <br />           requireSecurityContextCancellation =\"false\"&gt; <br />         &lt;secureConversationBootstrap authenticationMode=\"MutualCertificate\"&gt; <br />         &lt;/secureConversationBootstrap&gt; <br />      &lt;/security&gt; <br />      &lt;httpTransport/&gt; <br />    &lt;/binding&gt; <br />   &lt;/customBinding&gt;</pre>\n  <h1>Additional Resources</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>For more information see “How to: Create a Stateful Security Context Token for a Secure Session“ at <a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms731814.aspx\">http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms731814.aspx</a></li>\n  </ul>\n  <hr />\n  <p>Adapted from Microsoft patterns & practices guidance.</p>"
